{420}{}{Journalist's research}
{421}{}{The second world revolution, or The thing that has affected the humankind more than the Great War - the truth and the fiction.

At first I'd like to mention that within a couple of passed years the worst thing there can be has happened to the history of years 2242-2246 (If it'd have been forgotten - it would be a matter of time to find those who still know the facts), the information was still there but it rapidly changed and there occurred a lot of gossips, tales, myths and most worst of it - lies. I'm almost 100% sure that the Brotherhood of Steel as well as New Californian Republic (not to mention the Hubologists) has quite detailed information, however when I've turned to them with questions I was given such a classical reply that it has even survived through the Great War - ''No comments''. Therefore I could only rely on the stories of witnesses, or I'd say on the matching parts of their stories.


Exactly at midday of the 3rd of February, 2243 over all Hubologists' churches in all towns there have appeared posters saying - ''COMPLETE THE REDEMPTION AND YOU WILL BE HONORED'', ''REDEEM YOUR IMMORTAL SOUL'' and so on. There were priests on the streets convincing to complete the Redemption, assuring it won't bring any obligations, and if you join the Wheel by completing the Redemption, you will really help 'em. The masses have ignored the propaganda, but I was among those quite a few people who felt involved in some way… I personally got attracted by the fact that I won't mind completing the Redemption and it would help the priests, well, at least they say so, and there was another thing that played a role in my decision - I was not taking the Hubologists seriously (at that point) - seemed to me that people play games, however the organization survived through the Great War and still exists without any signs of trouble, priests walk in their robes through the Wasteland and so on, and it can be quite a reason to show some respect to them. In other words, I have completed my first Redemption on 05.02.2243. I was quite surprised by the procedure: I found myself on a table looking more like it was for repairing cars, however it was obvious that it was there for the procedure, but there was no equipment, no signs of machinery, Hubologists called it the Altar. Then they have covered me with a dark casing and for a minute I found myself in complete darkness. Afterwards I was told that after I die I'll be resurrected in the church I've completed the Redemption in, I asked something like ''That's a metaphor, isn't it?'', and the Hubologists replied that it's not and I will be resurrected as mentioned previously. It was getting dark when I walked out, despite I felt it has passed only 20 minutes and it was midday when I've entered the church… That's more or less the story told by most of the witnesses who completed the Redemption in February 2243. No one took the stories of resurrection for real (at that time it sounded too unbelievable), but almost everyone has told their friends of the new Hubologist's whim. I was intrigued by the procedure of the Redemption and asked one of my friends who felt attracted to Hubologists and completed the Redemption once. I was told that the exercise of the Redemption process has become canonic and therefore questions on why it is done exactly this way (or whether it has undergone any changes) are pointless.


It was at the end of February (I was in San-Fran) when I was sitting in one of the local pubs and heard of the Redemption process for the first time and that resurrection will follow after death. You could hear the laughter even outside of the building where the bar was located… 

This way by the end on February, according to my data, there were not more than 30-40 people who have completed the process of Redemption, you could hear rumors that Hubologists offer resurrection everywhere, however there was no evidence of it so people had their laugh and forgot about it… What I did is join a caravan in the beginning of March and head to Shady Sands, but we had bad luck after defending ourselves against some raider-freaks and stopped for an overnight break, while I was in charge, a deathclaw has approached me without a sound and killed me. Shock was all I felt when I found myself in the San-Francisco Hubologist's church. Seemed that they have pumped me with some tranquilizers to make sure I won't go insane and I kind of appreciate it, as I was pretty close to it. I could remember my death… It's impossible to describe. Moreover, the fact of resurrection taking place just couldn't fit into my vision of life. I was offered to complete the process of Redemption again, and, of course, I agreed. This time the process took really just around a minute. No one knew what has happened to the caravan and I did not tell anyone either, just my close friend have learned about it and, trusting my words, also went to the church to complete the Redemption. Most probably no one of those who were resurrected during the February-March 2243 period dared to tell about it because you'd have to prove it and I'm sure no one would like to find themselves in the church with fresh memories of their death again, at least not if it isn't critical enough. Luckily, everyone who has completed the Redemption procedure during that period told, just in case, that they will be resurrected after their death. This way there was a small flow of volunteers at the Hubologist's churches, mostly relatives and close friends of those who have already been resurrected.
At last by the end of March I've managed to reach Shady Sands and then New-Reno. There were talks about resurrection in every bar; however the overall mood was suspicious. And then the thing that would happen sooner or later anyway happened. One of the customers looking like a member of the local mafia, being drunk, started to tell that he has already died once and that the Hubologists have resurrected him. There were attempts to calm him down but he got even more excited, picking on everyone and asking whether they believe him or not. I simply looked in his eyes and said that I'm aware of it but one of the NCR rangers sitting nearby asked for a proof and offered a bet. As a result the bandit who has just shot himself in the mouth entered the bar from outside again, looking completely sober and dumbfound, and took the cash he won from the fainted ranger. By the way, I also won a couple of bets, as I was almost sure that this guy did not bluff.

Sooner or later such cases took place in all towns and people were finally convinced that resurrection is possible. I think the first period of integrating resurrection was completed by the end of 2243 when the fact of resurrection became well known. People had no choice but to deal with it, which was not an easy thing to do…

By the end of the year 2243 people in Modoc were called to boycott the Hubologists because most of the residents were afraid to take part in the Redemption procedure which terrifyingly changed the vision of life. Citizens even picketed for closure of the local church, but have not received any feedback within 3 weeks and calmed down. Two more weeks have passed when in the middle of September 2243 raiders started their raids growing into massive attacks, and the citizens realized that the Redemption is the only way to avoid serious losses in the defense.  This way boycott has ended under the influence of outside circumstances.

Straightforward aggression was addressed to Hubologists only (not a surprise) in New-Reno and Den. Representatives of minor gangs of New-Reno came to Hubologists' church to ask them to keep their rivals away from the Redemption procedure but received a short-spoken "No". The gangster were more offended not even by the denial but because they were not taken seriously and tried to attack the church. I had a chance to talk to one of the attackers who told me that everything started as usually (especially in New-Reno): jet, psycho, go-go-go, and after the grenades exploded and cleared the entrance and gang stormed into the church, they were professionally knocked out by people in robes. ''If my reaction would not be faster due to the effects of the combat drugs, I'd not understand who's knocked us down'', he said. What happened after is something he did not enjoy bringing up in his memory at all, I saw that he was having a hard time going on with the story: 'They've checked whether all of us had completed the Redemption and those who did not were forced to. After they made sure that all of us will be resurrected, they started to kill us, without emotions, and at the same time they were so cruel that I'd better have mercy and save my memory and ears and won't get into the detail, I'll just tell you what - each one of us died that many times that we could not even remember the figures. Afterwards we were set free and told that if we ever approach any of their churches again and keep a distance less than 10 meters, then the thing which just happened to us will feel like heaven in comparison to what's going to happen. Same attack took place at Den, the reasons remain unknown but the people say that a crowd of freaks imagined that they're cool and big and decided to attack the church. The outcome was the same as in New-Reno; almost 24 hours after the attack people noticed the attackers running for their lives…


This way the fact of resurrection was brought to the world almost without blood spilling, due to Wasteland's slow information flow resulting in news moving with caravans' speed many were planning to challenge the Hubologists' defense, but they were saved by the news from New-Reno and Den.

By the middle of 2244 the first (or less unfortunate) of those who have already completed the Redemption procedure have been resurrected 3 times. After the 3rd (most luckily) Redemption they have learned, that from now on Redemption has to be paid. The cost will be calculated with a help of a complex astrological formula, and for each one personally, and the cost will be a pretty high one. If it's true that from the 4th resurrection on you'll have to pay or not stayed unclear - some claimed that they had to pay from the 2nd resurrection, some claimed that they have had over 10 resurrections and never were asked to pay. I assume that you can be 95% sure that you'll pay after the 3rd Redemption. This way or another but people who have been resurrected for 3 times already faced a problem, the cost of Redemption. As among the first who've faced the problem were unstable people, who did not really care on how to get money and so a new type of crimes overflowed the region - crime for the sake of the Redemption.
 
The danger of dying without Redemption did not hinder those people who have died 3 times already; nothing could stop them from getting gold to pay for immortality. Government tried to push the Hubologists not to accept those who have committed crimes in order to receive Redemption but it has never had success. It has ended with policemen in front of each church, which has happened to be the best solution, as anyone who has committed a crime for Redemption's sake would sooner or later appear.

Afterwards, by the beginning of year 2245 when it was clear that the Hubologists wouldn't give any credit nor discount to anyone, caravans, while hiring security and then the government hiring armed forces (for example to fight the riders) have included the price for the Redemption in security's salary. It is unknown who has started it first but most probably different people started it simultaneously, however after this people refused to work in security if they weren't paid for the Redemption or they were not given an advance to cover the cost before a mission.

In the beginning of March, same year, Hubologists announced that they are willing to receive and save money people are going to pay for the Redemption (wouldn't matter whether the next one or any following ones) and Hubologists claimed that you can withdraw your money in any Hubologists' church. Almost everyone who had enough funds started to use this new benefit straight away. People started putting their cash on accounts in one city and took out in another so that they wouldn't tempt the raiders. Then lots of people started to take out cash only for certain needs and after a while started transferring money to each other instead of giving it from hand to hand…

Interesting fact is that the system, developed by the Hubologists, was functioning already very well by that time; however they have released their manifest only after the 24th of October, 2245. That's what one of them told me…

I personally think that they were acting step by step to avoid public resonance and soften the reaction of people on the Redemption and also to make the information flow regarding the procedure's nature as little as possible. First, there were rumors, then they were approved, then the people got proof of resurrection and only after people have calmed down the Hubologists made it commercial. It's unknown until now if that something that resurrects people is a technology or of a mystical nature, there's no answer on whether the Hubologists have used it before making public and on what date the first resurrection took place. Everyone is free to decide basing on the facts which I've brought up in my short research.


19.04.2246, San-Francisco}

# 43
#
{430}{}{Welcome!}
{431}{}{Welcome to the replication system!

Thank you for deciding to join the replication system of the Church of Hubology.
Perhaps you don't yet understand what's happening - right now you are in one of our replication centers, which means that not long ago you had the misfortune of dying somewhere in the not-so-friendly expanses of the Wasteland. And had it not been for your wise decision to undergo the initialization procedure, your spirit would already be far beyond the planet Terra.

Together with the initialization procedure, we performed a primary Zeta-scan and Purification, so you may now rightfully consider yourself an Active Hubo-Builder level 0, or simply AHB-0. We hope that you will express the desire to continue cooperating with the Church of Hubology, as well as take steps toward further Purification. Then we shall all be able to unite in the future in the spokes of the Great Wheel with our Heavenly Father.

We remind you that, due to the population's increased interest in the replication procedure, we have decided to abandon the policy of three free replications. Now only one, the first, demonstration replication is free, i.e. the one that brought you here. From now on the price will depend on the total number of replications and the relative complexity of replicating your body. For now the price of the first replication will be only 100 coins, which is essentially a gift. To transfer money to your replication account, visit one of our regional offices - they exist in all major cities. Try to maintain a positive account balance, otherwise upon your first death you will end up at a special replication station for debtors, from which you will not be able to leave until someone pays off your debt. Pay for replication on time! A prolonged stay among the inmates of the Special Station may cause irreparable harm to your neurodynes and forever deprive you of the chance to reunite with the Great Hub.

For your convenience, shops have been set up at the replication stations where you can purchase all the necessary equipment for a safe return home. Regular free transport from the stations to the nearest cities also runs.

We wish you luck in all your endeavors, and that you may have to visit our stations only by natural means.
Long live the Hub!


P.S. Dear replicant,

Unfortunately, your first replication did not go entirely smoothly. During the transition of your meta-ethereal shell, some inexplicable malfunction occurred and problems arose merging your ethereal and biological memory, due to which the data of the last several hours of your life were not copied into your new brain. I'm sorry, but this most likely means that you may not remember the reasons for the loss of your original bodily shell. With a small probability you may be in a state of partial amnesia - not remembering your name, your origin, not recognizing some relatives, but this information may be restored over time. We offer our deepest apologies for this unfortunate incident. I must assure you that this will not happen again in the future, and all those responsible will be found and punished.

As compensation, we have decided to give you a "Pip-Boy 2000" device, from the screen of which you are reading this message right now. This is Vault technology, recreated by us from prewar schematics. It usually sells for no less than $10,000, but you get it completely free of charge. You can use this device to keep records and read holodisks; it also has a reliable navigation system and a clock with an alarm built in. Also, for the convenience of replication users, the ability to check the balance of your replication account at any moment has been built in.

I hope this device will help you on your travels.

Respectfully,
AHB-5, administrator of your replication station.}

