{1090}{}{Vagabond's Disk}
{1091}{}{Recorded on this disk are the coordinates of the military facility that Tuco spoke about.}

#110
{1100}{}{Manual for the "Behemoth"-type Combat Machine}
{1101}{}{List of radio commands for controlling the combat machine:

"ROUTE" "X Coordinate" "Y Coordinate" - order to move to the settlement located at the specified coordinates.
"CAMERA" - connect your Pip-Boy to the machine's surveillance systems.
"MESSAGE" "*message text*" - broadcast the transmitted radio message at the machine's location.
"MOVE" "Number of steps" "direction" - order to begin moving in the specified direction for a certain number of steps. Possible directions: 0,1,2,3,4,5.
"PATROL" "Patrol radius" - set the mode of patrolling the surroundings. When an unknown appears within the specified radius relative to the machine's position, its description will be transmitted on the preset radio wave.
"CHANGECHANNEL" "Number of new radio channel" - switch the preset frequency to a new wave.
"ATTACK" - activate the machine's combat mode.

To transmit commands, use the preset radio frequency.
Begin all commands with the keyword "COMMAND".
}

